description: Kuwait has handed its annual $2 million contribution to the U.N. Relief and Works Agency for Palestinian refugees (UNRWA), the Kuwaiti state news agency KUNA reported on Thursday.
title: Kuwait hands $2 million to UNRWA for 2024, state news agency says

description: Gang violence in Haiti has killed over 1,500 people so far this year while dozens have been lynched by so-called self-defence brigades, the U.N. human rights office said on Thursday.
title: Haiti gang violence deaths surge in 2024, UN report says

description: At least 32,552 Palestinians have been killed and 74,980 injured in Israel's military offensive in the Gaza Strip since Oct. 7, the Palestinian enclave's health ministry said on Thursday.
title: 32,552 Palestinians killed in Gaza since Oct. 7, health ministry says

description: Less than a minute before Baltimore's Francis Scott Key Bridge collapsed from the impact of a colliding cargo ship, a first responder on emergency radio answered the crew's mayday call by sending officers to halt traffic onto the bridge.
title: Baltimore bridge collapse: What warnings preceded the ship's crash?

description: Brazil's former President Jair Bolsonaro told Supreme Court Justice Alexandre de Moraes on Wednesday he had no reason to have sought asylum at the Hungarian embassy, after the court summoned him to explain why he stayed at the diplomatic compound for two nights in February.
title: Bolsonaro tells Supreme Court he did not seek asylum at Hungarian embassy

description: Bosnian Serb separatist leader Milorad Dodik said on Thursday that Serbs would block the work of Bosnia's national government unless election laws imposed by an international envoy are annulled and Western ambassadors expelled from the country.
title: Bosnian Serb leader Dodik threatens to block national government

description: The Brazilian President Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva said on Thursday that the trade deal which Mercosur and the European Union blocs have been negotiating looks more promising than a previous version.
title: Brazil's Lula says current EU-Mercosur deal negotiations look more promising than before

description: Britain's government has ended its push to use increases in the minimum wage to narrow the gap between the lowest earners and those on higher pay, offering some relief to employers after this year's nearly 10% jump.
title: Britain to slow rise of minimum wage from 2025, government says

description: Bulgaria's populist There Is Such a People (ITN) party declined on Thursday to try to form a new national government, paving the way for President Rumen Radev to call snap elections.
title: Bulgaria's populists reject mandate to form government, set stage for snap vote

description: South Africa's Department of Transport on Thursday said a bus crash near Mamatlakala in the northern province of Limpopo resulted in at least 45 deaths and one seriously injured person.
title: Bus accident in South Africa kills at least 45, Transport Ministry says

description: Russian artist Alyona Kazinskaya likes to fill her social media feed with cheerful messages and vivid floral paintings. For 30 minutes last Friday night, it turned into a timeline of terror.
title: Caught up in concert shooting, a Russian woman said goodbye to the world

description: China hopes the Netherlands would support companies in fulfilling their contractual obligations and ensure "normal" trade of lithography machines, said Chinese Commerce Minister Wang Wentao.
title: China hopes Netherlands will ensure 'normal' lithography machine trade

description: Spanish coastguards rescued 124 migrants, including young children and a person needing a wheelchair, from two wooden boats in the seas off the Canary Islands on Thursday.
title: Coastguards rescue 124 migrants off Spain's Canary Islands

description: The collapse of Baltimore's Key Bridge has highlighted what engineers say is an urgent need to better protect the piers holding up spans over shipping channels as the size of cargo ships has grown in recent decades.
title: Collapse highlights need to protect critical foundations

description: Colombia ordered the expulsion of Argentine diplomats from their embassy in the Andean nation, Colombia's foreign ministry said on Wednesday, citing "denigrating" comments by Argentine President Javier Milei about Colombian President Gustavo Petro.
title: Colombia expels Argentine diplomats after Milei calls Petro 'terrorist'

description: An Indian court extended the custody of opposition leader and Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal until April 1 on Thursday in a graft case related to the national capital territory's liquor policy, local media said.
title: Delhi Chief Minister Kejriwal's custody extended until April 1 in graft case

description: Dengue cases in the Americas spiked in the first three months of this year by three times the number of infections reported in the same period last year, the Pan American Health Organization said on Thursday.
title: Dengue cases surge in the Americas in potentially worst-ever outbreak -PAHO

description: Difficulties getting Israeli permission for foreign staff to work in Israel and the Palestinian territories are hampering efforts to get aid into war-shattered Gaza where civilians are facing imminent famine, according to U.N. data and aid workers.
title: Dozens of stalled Israeli visas seen hindering Gaza aid efforts

description: Economist Joaquim Miranda Sarmento was named Portugal's new finance minister on Thursday as President Marcelo Rebelo de Sousa approved the formation of a centre-right minority government.
title: Economist Miranda Sarmento named Portugal's new finance minister

description: Population growth in Egypt, the Arab world's most populous country, slowed to 1.4% in 2023, its lowest rate in decades, the planning ministry said on Thursday.
title: Egypt population growth continues slowing to 1.4%, government says

description: The head of Estonia's military said on Thursday that his country needs to double defence spending over the next two years to stockpile enough munitions to inflict a decisive defeat on any Russian invasion force.
title: Estonia must double defence spending to counter Russia, military chief says

description: Fiji's former long-serving prime minister Frank Bainimarama has avoided jail and was discharged by the High Court on Thursday, after earlier this month being found guilty of perverting the court of justice, local media reported.
title: Former Fiji leader Bainimarama avoids jail in court case sentencing

description: France will provide over 30 million euros ($32.41 million) to United Nations Palestinian refugee agency UNRWA this year to support its operations amid the devastating war in Gaza, said the foreign ministry in Paris.
title: France to provide UNRWA funding ensuring right conditions are met - foreign ministry

description: France's lower house of parliament approved legislation on Thursday to outlaw discrimination against dreadlocks, braids, afros and any other hair style, colour or texture, defeating some who called the bill an unnecessary import of U.S. ideas.
title: French lawmakers vote to outlaw discrimination against afros and braids

description: The government of Greek Prime Minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis faces a no-confidence vote on Thursday over the handling of a train crash last year that killed 57 people, after media reports emerged this week alleging manipulation of evidence.
title: Greek PM faces no-confidence vote over 2023 train crash

description: Nearly 500 immigration and human rights organizations signed a letter urging the U.S. government to halt deportations of Haitians and expand migration protections as a devastating gang conflict escalates on the Caribbean island nation.
title: Hundreds of rights groups urge US to stop deporting Haitians fleeing gang war

description: Hungarian prosecutors are investigating statements made by a former government insider alleging attempts to influence a graft case, and have heard former justice minister Judit Varga as a witness, a chief prosecutor said on Thursday.
title: Hungary prosecutors probe graft case tape leaked by former government insider

description: India is open to being a part of trading blocs which include China if Beijing ensures its economy is open, transparent, and complies with the rules of the World Trade Organisation, India's trade minister Piyush Goyal said at a media event on Thursday.
title: India open to joining trade blocs with China if its economy is WTO compliant, trade minister says

description: The legal team of Indonesia's president-elect Prabowo Subianto said on Thursday the losing presidential candidates' bid in the country's top court to disqualify him would negate the people's right to vote.
title: Indonesia president-elect's legal team rebuffs losing candidates' bid to disqualify him

description: The spokesperson for Islamic State praised the group's attack that killed more than 140 people in a Russian concert hall near Moscow.
title: Islamic State spokesperson praises group's attack on concert hall in Russia

description: The United States' top general said on Thursday that Israel had not received every weapon that it has asked for, in part because President Joe Biden's administration was not willing to provide at least some of them.
title: Israel has not received everything it has asked for, top US general says

description: An Israeli court on Thursday ruled that a former Mexican diplomat who has been accused of sexual abuse and rape in one of his home country's most prominent #MeToo cases is extraditable.
title: Israeli court rules Mexican ex-diplomat accused of rape extraditable

description: Israeli soldiers have been posting photos and videos of themselves toying with lingerie found in Palestinian homes, creating a dissonant visual record of the war in Gaza as a looming famine intensifies world scrutiny of Israel's offensive.
title: Israeli soldiers play with Gaza women's underwear in online posts

description: An Italian woman charged in Hungary with taking part in an anti-fascist group's assaults on people they viewed as far-right activists will remain in jail after a judge denied her attorney's request that she be released into house arrest.
title: Italian woman held in Hungary to remain in jail

description: Indonesia's parliament on Thursday designated special status for Jakarta, keeping the metropolis as the country's economic epicentre, amid plans to move the capital city to Borneo island.
title: Jakarta to remain economic hub as Indonesia prepares to move capital city

description: King Charles, who is undergoing treatment for cancer, has praised people who "extend the hand of friendship, especially in a time of need", and echoed the pledge to serve the nation that the British monarch made at his coronation last year.
title: King Charles praises 'hand of friendship' in Maundy Thursday message

description: The Kremlin said on Thursday complete silence was needed when it came to discussions about possible prisoner exchanges involving Evan Gershkovich, a Wall Street Journal reporter arrested in Russia a year ago on suspicion of espionage.
title: Kremlin says silence essential for any Gershkovich prisoner exchange

description: The Kremlin told Telegram owner Pavel Durov to be more attentive after the messaging application was allegedly used to help recruit the gunmen who attacked a concert hall outside Moscow.
title: Kremlin tells Telegram owner: be more attentive after attack near Moscow

description: Ukraine asked Western allies for air defence supplies at an extraordinary meeting of the NATO-Ukraine Council on Thursday after a spate of Russian missile attacks on critical and energy infrastructure, Ukraine's mission to NATO said.
title: Kyiv asks NATO partners for air defence supplies after Russia hits energy system

description: Security measures in the Ukrainian capital Kyiv will be tightened after a spate of Russian ballistic missile attacks and threats of escalation, a city official said on Thursday.
title: Kyiv to tighten security after ballistic missile attacks

description: Kyrgyz people working in Russia are being actively targeted by recruiters of militant groups who want them to carry out violent acts, Kyrgyzstan's labour ministry said on Thursday.
title: Kyrgyzstan says its citizens in Russia are targeted by militant recruiters

description: Latvian Foreign Minister Krisjanis Karins said he would leave his post from April 10, Latvian public broadcaster LSM reported on Thursday.
title: Latvian foreign minister resigns, Latvian public broadcaster says

description: The owner, operator and charterer of the container ship that struck Baltimore’s Francis Scott Key Bridge on Tuesday are likely to face lawsuits over its collapse and the people killed or injured, but legal experts say U.S. maritime law could limit the companies’ liability.
title: Lawsuits over Baltimore bridge collapse likely, though limited, lawyers say

description: Malaysia's government has said it would consider extending a $10 billion China-led rail project to its border with Thailand to boost economic ties between the Southeast Asian neighbours.
title: Malaysia open to extending China-led rail project to Thai border

description: Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu asked Israel's top court on Thursday to defer a deadline for the government to come up with a new military conscription plan that would address mainstream anger at the exemptions granted to ultra-Orthodox Jews.
title: Netanyahu asks Israeli court to defer deadline on conscription controversy

description: Nigeria's military will free more than 300 people suspected of being part of the Boko Haram Islamist insurgency after a court ruled there was no evidence they committed any crimes, a defence spokesperson said on Thursday.
title: Nigeria to free 313 suspected Boko Haram insurgents for lack of evidence

description: President Joe Biden will get a boost from Democratic predecessors Barack Obama and Bill Clinton on Thursday at a fundraiser in New York slated to raise more than $25 million and add some oomph to Biden's 2024 re-election campaign.
title: Obama, Bill Clinton to join Biden to raise $25 million at event with Queen Latifah and Lizzo

description: Pakistan will set up an inquiry commission to investigate accusations by six High Court judges of interference and intimidation by the country's powerful intelligence agencies in judicial decisions, the law minister said on Thursday.
title: Pakistan to investigate army's meddling in judiciary, law minister says

description: Israeli forces and Palestinian fighters battled in close combat around Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital on Thursday, where the armed wings of Hamas and Islamic Jihad said they attacked Israeli soldiers and tanks with rockets and mortar fire
title: Palestinian fighters battle Israeli forces around Gaza's Al Shifa Hospital

description: Palestinian Prime Minister Mohammad Mustafa formed a new cabinet on Thursday in which he will also serve as foreign minister, replacing Riyad al-Maliki, Palestinian news agency WAFA reported.
title: Palestinian PM Mustafa forms new cabinet, to serve as foreign minister too

description: The Philippines will implement countermeasures proportionate and reasonable against "illegal, coercive, aggressive, and dangerous attacks" by China's coastguard and maritime militia in the South China Sea, President Ferdinand Marcos Jr. said on Thursday.
title: Philippines' Marcos vows countermeasures in response to Chinese 'attacks'

description: Poland's Internal Security Agency (ABW) has carried out searches as part of an investigation with other European security services into alleged Russian espionage, it said on Thursday.
title: Poland investigating Russian espionage, security agency says

description: Poland notified its NATO allies "well in advance" of the dismissal of a Eurocorps commander over a security matter and they showed no concern, the defence minister said on Thursday.
title: Poland told allies in advance about dismissal of Eurocorps commander, minister says

description: Poland and Ukraine are closer to reaching an agreement regarding agricultural imports, the Polish prime minister said on Thurdsay after intergovernmental talks, as Warsaw seeks to defuse farmers' protests.
title: Poland, Ukraine close to agreement on food imports, says Tusk

description: Pope Francis looked well as he began four intense days of events leading to Easter on Thursday, and renewed his own ordination vow on the day the Roman Catholic Church marks Jesus's founding of the priesthood the night before the crucifixion.
title: Pope, looking healthy, begins busy four days leading to Easter

description: Pope Francis looked well as he washed and kissed the feet of 12 women prisoners on Thursday at a traditional ritual on the first of four event-filled days leading to Easter for the 87-year-old pontiff.
title: Pope, looking well, visits female prison for foot-washing ritual

description: If Western countries supply Ukraine with F-16 fighters, the aircraft will not alter the situation on the battlefield, Russian news agencies quoted President Vladimir Putin as telling military pilots on Wednesday.
title: Putin tells pilots: F16s can carry nuclear weapons but they won't change things in Ukraine

description: Russia vetoed on Thursday the annual renewal of a panel of experts monitoring enforcement of longstanding United Nations sanctions against North Korea over its nuclear weapons and ballistic missile programs.
title: Russia blocks renewal of North Korea sanctions monitors

description: Russian investigators said on Thursday they had uncovered evidence that the gunmen who killed more than 140 people in an attack on a concert hall near Moscow last week were linked to "Ukrainian nationalists".
title: Russia says evidence links concert hall attackers to "Ukrainian nationalists"

description: A Russian military aircraft crashed into the sea on Thursday off the Crimean port of Sevastopol, the Russian-installed governor of the region said.
title: Russian military plane crashes in sea off Crimea - local governor

description: Water has almost completely flooded the Pioneer gold mine in Russia's Amur region, where 13 miners are stuck, Russia's state-run RIA Novosti news agency said on Thursday, citing emergency services.
title: Russian mine with 13 trapped miners almost completely flooded, RIA reports

description: Legislation that would that would allow people living in Scotland with a terminal illness to take their own lives was laid before the country's parliament on Thursday as a poll showed the policy is backed by most of the population.
title: Scotland's parliament considers assisted dying as poll shows support

description: Bus drivers in the South Korean capital of Seoul ended an hours-long strike on Thursday after a deal was reached between the city's bus union and its employers over a wage hike, easing the commute for the city of more than 9 million people.
title: Seoul bus drivers end strike after city agrees to wage increase

description: Taiwan's foreign ministry said on Thursday it believes U.S. support will remain unchanged no matter who wins the presidential election, but it will stay on guard for Taiwan-China issues being "manipulated" as the campaign heats up.
title: Taiwan sees US support unchanged no matter who wins election

description: Bruised and fractured by Tayyip Erdogan's victory in 2023 general elections, Turkey's opposition aims to land a blow in Sunday's local polls, with the future of its biggest hope, Istanbul Mayor Ekrem Imamoglu, tied to the outcome.
title: Turkey local election: opposition aims to hit back at Erdogan

description: Turkey holds municipal elections across 81 provinces on Sunday March 31, with President Tayyip Erdogan's AK Party (AKP) aiming to reclaim cities it lost in 2019, including the country's largest city of Istanbul and the capital Ankara.
title: Turkey's local election: a test for Erdogan and his rival Imamoglu

description: Two children are among at least six people who have been detained or questioned in Russia over online comments viewed as "justifying terrorism" since last week's deadly attack on a concert hall, according to local authorities and Russian media.
title: Two children among Russians questioned over 'terrorism' posts

description: Aminchon Islomov and his father Isroil Islomov, two of eight suspects detained over suspected involvement in the Moscow concert hall attack last week, have appealed their pre-trial detention, Russian state news agency RIA reported on Thursday.
title: Two suspects in Moscow concert hall attack appeal pre-trial detention, RIA says

description: Ukrainian forces shot down 26 out of 28 attack drones launched overnight by Russia, Kyiv's military said on Thursday.
title: Ukraine destroys 26 Russian drones in latest overnight strike

description: Ukrainian Foreign Minister Dmytro Kuleba said he had arrived in New Delhi on Thursday to advance Kyiv's vision of the path to peace in Ukraine and to strengthen ties with India.
title: Ukraine foreign minister visits India to build support for peace blueprint

description: Britain’s greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions fell by 5.4% in 2023 partly due to lower gas use in the electricity sector, provisional government data showed on Thursday.
title: UK's greenhouse gas emissions fell 5.4% in 2023, government data shows

description: The United Nations Human Rights Committee urged Britain on Thursday to abandon a contentious bill to deport refugees to Rwanda, which could become law next month.
title: UN rights committee urges UK to drop plan to deport refugees to Rwanda

description: The U.N. Human Rights Committee said on Thursday it was concerned by extrajudicial killings in Indonesia's Papua province, where separatists and Indonesian troops have been fighting for decades.
title: UN rights panel concerned by extrajudicial killings in Indonesia's Papua

description: The United States warned on Thursday that it would push the U.N. Security Council to take action to get aid to starving people in Sudan, possibly by authorizing cross-border deliveries from Chad, if the Sudanese armed forces do not restore full access.
title: US urges UN Security Council action to get aid into Sudan from Chad

description: Russia's Investigative Committee says it has evidence that the Tajik gunmen accused of killing at least 143 people at a concert hall near Moscow last week were linked to Ukrainian nationalists. Ukraine denies involvement, and the U.S. says Islamic State - which claimed the attack - bears sole responsibility.
title: What do we know about the suspects in the Russian concert shooting?

description: The White House on Thursday dismissed as "nonsense" Russia's charge of Ukraine's involvement in last week's attack on Moscow's Crocus City concert hall that claimed more than 140 lives, saying it was clear that Islamic State was "solely responsible."
title: White House says US passed written warning of Moscow attack to Russia

description: Judges at the International Court of Justice on Thursday unanimously ordered Israel to take all the necessary and effective action to ensure basic food supplies arrive without delay to the Palestinian population in Gaza.
title: World court orders Israel to take action to address Gaza famine

description: The feasts and festivities of the Muslim holy month of Ramadan have been muted in Sudan this year with millions of people displaced from their homes and struggling with hunger as a war between the army and paramilitaries nears the one-year mark.
title: Year-long war dims Sudan's Ramadan festivities

description: President Volodymyr Zelenskiy told the speaker of the U.S. House of Representatives during a phone call on Thursday that it was vital that Congress passes a new military aid package for Kyiv rapidly.
title: Zelenskiy tells U.S. House speaker: quick passage of military aid is vital
